TI  - Albumin decrement in depression and cholesterol decrement in mania.
PG  - 173-6
AB  - Within all psychiatric inpatients over a 4-year period, on admission depressives 
      showed serum albumin 5.4% lower (P less than 0.001) than non-psychiatric 
      controls. Similarly, manics showed cholesterol 10% lower (P less than 0.0005) and 
      serum calcium/protein ratio 2.2% higher (P less than 0.05) than controls. These 
      deviations suggest a tendency towards dietary aberrations in these patients of 
      potential medical significance. These tests had shown the most distinct variation 
      with diagnosis on split-half discriminant function analysis of routine chemistry 
      and hematology tests of 107 patients with mania, 132 with depression, 67 with 
      schizophrenia, 18 with schizoaffective illness, and 83 non-psychiatric controls 
      admitted for elective surgery.
