TI  - The effects of vitamin A toxicity on calcium and lipid metabolism in chronic 
      renal failure.
PG  - 573-8
AB  - Serum vitamin A levels were high in haemodialysis patients, and were found to 
      correlate with plasma calcium, triglyceride, cholesterol and insulin levels. 
      Vitamin A containing multivitamin supplements were found to contribute to 
      increased serum vitamin A levels, and their withdrawal in seven patients caused a 
      significant decrease in serum vitamin A and calcium levels, with no effect on 
      lipid levels. Vitamin A containing preparations should therefore be prescribed 
      with caution in these patients.
